 Jeffreys Bay - The number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in the Kouga region has increased to 32, according to the latest report from the Department of Health. "13 of the 32 cases are active while 19 have already recovered," the Kouga Local Municipality said. "All 13 patients are in self-quarantine." It added that the active cases are in Humansdorp (7), Jeffreys Bay (4), St Francis Bay (1) and Hankey (1). "No further details were released." Meanwhile, as of Wednesday, COVID-19 cases in the Eastern Cape stood at 7 154. The Province has 3 647 recoveries. Regrettably, the Province has lost another nine (9) patients to Covid-19. "We send our deepest sympathies to their loved ones and thank the healthcare workers who treated the patients," said Eastern Cape Premier, Oscar Mabuyane. "The total number of deaths is now at 147." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  